South Africa Calls for Greater IMF Influence for Emerging Market Countries

-- B y   G o r d o n   B e l l
-- 
2011-06-29T13:55:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-29/south-africa-calls-for-greater-imf-influence-for-emerging-market-countries.html
South African Finance Minister
 Pravin Gordhan  congratulated  Christine Lagarde  on her
appointment as managing director of the International Monetary
Fund and said she must now work on improving the representation
of emerging markets in the institution.  Gordhan commented in an e-mailed statement today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gordon Bell at 
 gbell16@bloomberg.net  